attribs.name: marquee
attribs.current:
Clan Ravnos of India descends from Zapathasura of the Third Generation, whose sire is unknown.
Nomads, tricksters and performers, they have long been villified as con-artists and deceivers.  Armed
with unparalleled powers of illusion, the very senses turn traitor in the presence of a Ravnos.

attribs.name: bp_slaketext
attribs.current:
Animals & bagged blood slake half Hunger.
Humans slake full Hunger.
Must kill to reduce Hunger below 1.

attribs.name: bane_text
attribs.current: Your afflicted Malkavian lineage is cursed with one or more mental derangements:  You may experience delusions, visions of terrible clarity, or something entirely different. When you suffer a Bestial Failure or a Compulsion, your deranged nature manifests and you suffer a penalty equal to your Bane Severity (1) to one category of dice pools (Physical, Social, or Mental) for the entire scene.

attribs.name: repeating_beliefs_-LN8NjD7tcGK21eDrTrT_conviction
attribs.current: Everyone Deserves Healing, But Not For Free

attribs.name: repeating_beliefs_-LN8PltMGds9c8ZtUDFd_touchstone_details
attribs.current:
The MD with whom I completed my doctorate.  Now senile and in a retirement home.  Believes he's talking with his student's ghost, but doesn't really mind.
Antoine LaGritte was a thoroughly rational man when I studied under him, and even now in the grips of old age and senility he is remarkably accepting of new conclusions when proof is presented to him.
Visiting has become risky though, as he resides squarely inside of Scheer's territory.

attribs.name: repeating_beliefs_-LN8Og-FVj8tGAzq5bqB_touchstone_details
attribs.current:
Boss of the "Bookies" street gang, which primarily deal in protection and party drugs on the UofT campus.  Known for being a 'straight' man who keeps his word and treats his people fairly.  Some neighboring gangs think that makes him weak, but that ignores Greene's expertise in wielding that reputation.  The Bookies are seen as the most trustworthy and reliable way to get anything they offer, and tales of his rival bosses' excesses and betrayals abound.

Once upon a time, I saved his life from a gut wound.

attribs.name: repeating_beliefs_-LN8NjD7tcGK21eDrTrT_touchstone_details
attribs.current:
Nurse Mary, who Johannes worked closely with at one point, is the most generous giving person he knows.  She works frequent overtime to support her family of 5, all of whom are unemployed adults who seem intent on wasting her money and her kindness.
She now works in the hospital currently owned by the MIB.

attribs.current: 128 XP Earned - 118 XP Spent =  10 XP Remaining

attribs.current: Initial XP awarded at the beginning of the Chronicle.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LON8tOnZzipo2o5r3FL_advantage_details
attribs.current: The baroness values your coterie quite highly, but her support is unreliable: The duties of her office demand much of her time, not to mention how difficult it can be to contact her given her frequent relocations and security precautions.

attribs.name: repeating_negadvantage_-LON8yJbUw5j-8WZZ73d_negadvantage_details
attribs.current: Frederik Scheer, elder of Clan Tremere and Camarilla seneschal of Toronto, has not ceded any part of his city to the Anarchs.  The erosion of Camarilla power has only intensified his fervor: Toronto will remain the Camarilla stronghold it always has been, whatever it takes.  Unfortunately for you, his attentions are firmly fixed on your coterie --- not only are you the baroness' most prized with two of her childer among its members, but your recent activities have proven to be a thorn in Scheer's side one too many times.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LNfoRKGIZH5kARB0CAK_advantage_details
attribs.current: Ogden Stone is an employee at Riddick Pharmaceuticals that has always wanted just a bit more- of money, of time, of respect, and he isn't very particular about how he gets it.  Luckily for his employers, he's a small man with little imagination, so he sticks to 'losing' a few shipments and salvaging excess reactants from research.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LNfoNRubhG6L-LSUk4z_advantage_details
attribs.current:
4 dots: Effectiveness,  2 dots: Reliability

The Bookies are a street gang that controls the area in and around the University of Toronto main campus.  Due to the multitudes of students there they find ample fodder for their party drugs and white-collar crime, and even a small protection racket.

attribs.name: repeating_negadvantage_-LNfotZCc3YTE1T2aucG_negadvantage_details
attribs.current: I died a bloody death in the hospital morgue while removing a large shard of wood from the heart of a corpse.  Some med student was with me at the time; hope they got out ok.

attribs.name: repeating_negadvantage_-LNfob-WnfbUfNPeMfYh_negadvantage_details
attribs.current: James Underwood was a med student when he witnessed a corpse tear out the throat of the doctor he was working with.  He had almost convinced himself that he was wrong (about it being a corpse, about the teeth, the blood) when he saw that same Dr. Napier on the street while leaving his usual bar.

attribs.name: repeating_negadvantage_-LNfof5lsygzn9NVE-fS_negadvantage_details
attribs.current: In his time as a vampire, Johannes has found it most convenient and circumspect to dose his prospective victims with a painkiller or two to cover up the sting and explain away the other sensations.  Unfortunately, while the tactic is a good one, he seems to have acquired a bit of a taste for the stuff.

attribs.name: domain_hunt
attribs.current: Johannes Napier feeds primarily from his patients (while they're doped up) and on his stores of blood harvested in a similar manner.  Most of his diet is tainted by painkillers due to the way he treats his patients.

attribs.name: ambition
attribs.current: To cut through the lies and superstitions that surround the vampiric condition and unearth the true source and cause.  Maybe then we can purge this unruly beast from our veins.

attribs.name: mask
attribs.current: John Nale, back-alley doctor who serves the patrons and contestants of a particular fight club, as well as anyone willing to pay.

attribs.name: mortal_ambition
attribs.current: To lessen the strain on the wounded and ill, and make a good living off of it.

attribs.name: mortal_history
attribs.current: Johannes Napier was born in the outskirts of Frankfurt, Germany, but moved to the united states at the tender age of 3.  He did well in school, showcasing a keen mind and an unflappable nature that would serve him well in his chosen field.  Napier chose to become a doctor at 17, reasoning that it was the most profitable method of helping others.  Exposure to the real world has jaded him somewhat since then, dampening the altruism and replacing it with an irritated desire to "cut the bullshit".  He isn't known for his bedside manner, but his calm demeanor certainly helps worried patients and his needle and scalpel rarely miss their marks.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LSm-8wAJUiF7ngRf6Po_advantage_details
attribs.current: Hemovore Physiology: You may not know Netchurch, or even know of him, but you have started upon the path of demystifying the vampiric condition.  Once per session you may ask a question about vampire or ghoul biology or physiology.  Depending on the relevancy of the answer you may also receive a +1 die bonus on a single die roll.  If the Storyteller chooses not to answer your question or makes you roll for it, you are entitled to one further question.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LTL4RT5OrFgHsOUUaEY_advantage_details
attribs.current: Over the course of a year, Dr. Napier medically aided the Bookies against another gang's incursion.  The gang as a whole, as well as a number of its members owe him a great deal because not only did he save their lives, he also accepted blood donations in lieu of payment, saving them the money they desperately needed to fight back.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-Lbu5yp8uxbJqDDYlK1k_advantage_details
attribs.current: Examined Afflictions: It’s a well-kept secret, but vampires are not so far from the afflictions of mortals as they like to believe.  Drugs and drink are transferred—and enjoyed—via the blood, but certain other chemicals, diseases and concoctions can also taint a meal.  You know how to formulate and diagnose vampire-specific diseases and poisons, some of which are normally undetectable in the blood or leave humans nearly unharmed.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LgPv-Z9JHKDqeNGiVIg_advantage_details
attribs.current: Postmortem Surgery: You own a copy of one of Netchurch’s more widely-available papers, which investigates the nature of vampiric healing and the integrity of the body after the Embrace.  Though you may shudder to think of the experiments required to test some of these conclusions, they are not without use.  By conducting a lengthy, costly operation (that isn’t without risk), you may apply Medicine to heal Aggravated Health damage in vampires as if they were mortal. The patient need not expend vitae to heal, but an equivalent amount of vampiric vitae is consumed over the course of the procedure.
